    "scriptPackage":  {
                          "narrationScript":  "Pause is not pivot. The Fed held the target range at 3.50 to 3.75 percent. The catch is that a hold can look calm while the message stays restrictive. Trigger: inflation is still too far above target for the Fed to declare victory. Transmission: if the cut path stays conditional, rate-sensitive trades still have to clear a high bar. The proof is the gap: PCE inflation is 4.1 percent versus the Fed\u0027s 2 percent target. So the next thing to watch is not only the next Fed headline. It is PCE, the 2-year yield, Fed language, and growth multiples. A pause was the decision. The pivot still needs proof. For news and education, not individualized investment advice.",
